---
// The Challenge section for Healthcare industry page
---

<section id="challenge" class="cre-challenge-section">
  <div class="cre-challenge-container">
    <span class="section-label">THE CHALLENGE</span>
    <h2 class="cre-challenge-headline">
      Speed vs. quality in healthcare
    </h2>
    <p class="cre-challenge-subheadline">
      Healthcare organizations move fast out of necessity. Patients need care immediately. Insurance approvals are time-sensitive. But most healthcare providers are still running on paper records, manual processes, and disconnected systems that create bottlenecks and errors.
    </p>

    <!-- Highlight Box -->
    <div class="cre-highlight-box">
      <p class="cre-highlight-text">
        "The average healthcare provider loses 25-35% of potential patient volume because they can't process intake and schedule appointments fast enough."
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Challenge List -->
    <div class="cre-challenge-list-wrapper">
      <ul class="cre-challenge-list">
        <li><strong>Patient intake is fragmented</strong> across paper forms, online portals, and manual data entry—making it impossible to capture complete information and creating duplicate records.</li>
        <li><strong>Clinical workflows depend on manual handoffs</strong> between departments. Clinicians spend hours searching for patient data across disconnected systems instead of focusing on care delivery.</li>
        <li><strong>Insurance verification is manual and time-consuming</strong>, requiring staff to call insurers, verify coverage, and update patient records—delaying care and frustrating both patients and providers.</li>
        <li><strong>Appointment scheduling is inefficient</strong>, with no visibility into provider availability or patient queue status—leading to no-shows, cancellations, and wasted capacity.</li>
        <li><strong>Clinical documentation is reactive</strong> instead of automated. Clinicians spend time typing notes instead of seeing patients, burning out staff and limiting patient throughput.</li>
        <li><strong>Operational metrics are opaque</strong> because reporting requires manual data pulls from multiple EMR systems, delaying visibility into performance, quality metrics, and revenue cycle issues.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Stat Cards -->
    <div class="cre-stat-cards">
      <div class="cre-stat-card">
        <div class="cre-stat-number">25-35%</div>
        <div class="cre-stat-label">patient volume lost</div>
      </div>
      <div class="cre-stat-card">
        <div class="cre-stat-number">45+ mins</div>
        <div class="cre-stat-label">per patient intake</div>
      </div>
      <div class="cre-stat-card">
        <div class="cre-stat-number">3-5 days</div>
        <div class="cre-stat-label">insurance verification</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .cre-challenge-section {
    background: #FFFFFF;
    padding: clamp(30px, 4vw, 50px) 24px;
  }

  .cre-challenge-container {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .section-label {
    display: block;
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #000000;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .cre-challenge-headline {
    font-family: 'Figtree', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(40px, 5vw, 56px);
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.2;
    color: #000000;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .cre-challenge-subheadline {
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7);
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    max-width: 900px;
  }

  .cre-highlight-box {
    background: rgba(14, 165, 233, 0.05);
    border-left: 4px solid #0EA5E9;
    padding: 32px;
    margin-bottom: 48px;
  }

  .cre-highlight-text {
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #000000;
    font-style: italic;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .cre-challenge-list-wrapper {
    margin-bottom: 64px;
  }

  .cre-challenge-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 20px;
  }

  .cre-challenge-list li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 32px;
    font-size: 17px; /* Increased from 16px for better readability */
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7);
  }

  .cre-challenge-list li::before {
    content: '−';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: #0EA5E9;
    font-size: 24px;
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .cre-challenge-list li strong {
    font-size: 17px; /* Match parent font size */
    color: #000000;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .cre-stat-cards {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 20px;
  }

  .cre-stat-card {
    background: rgba(14, 165, 233, 0.05);
    border: 1px solid rgba(14, 165, 233, 0.2);
    padding: 32px;
    text-align: center;
    transition: all 0.4s ease;
  }

  .cre-stat-card:hover {
    background: rgba(14, 165, 233, 0.1);
    border-color: rgba(14, 165, 233, 0.4);
  }

  .cre-stat-number {
    font-size: clamp(32px, 4vw, 48px);
    font-weight: 400;
    color: #0EA5E9;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .cre-stat-label {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7);
    text-transform: lowercase;
  }

  @media (max-width: 1024px) {
    .cre-challenge-list {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .cre-challenge-list li {
      font-size: 16px; /* Slightly smaller on tablet */
    }

    .cre-challenge-list li strong {
      font-size: 16px; /* Match tablet size */
    }

    .cre-stat-cards {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .cre-challenge-section {
      padding: clamp(20px, 3vw, 40px) 24px;
    }

    .cre-challenge-list li {
      font-size: 15px; /* Original size on mobile for space efficiency */
    }

    .cre-challenge-list li strong {
      font-size: 15px; /* Match mobile size */
    }

    .cre-highlight-box {
      padding: 24px;
    }

    .cre-stat-card {
      padding: 24px;
    }
  }
</style>

